# HBMP Docs Platform - Cursor Rules

## Context
You are helping build a monorepo called hbmp-docs-platform for managing business documentation.

## Architecture Rules

### Backend (/server)
- Node.js 20, TypeScript, Express
- Prisma ORM with SQLite (file: server/prisma/dev.db)
- REST APIs as specified in docs/api-spec.md
- Listen on port 4000
- Enable CORS for http://localhost:5173
- Use proper error handling and validation

### Frontend (/client)
- React 18+ with Vite
- TypeScript
- shadcn/ui components + Tailwind CSS
- React Router for navigation
- Functional components with hooks
- Connect to backend at http://localhost:4000/api

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strictly (no `any` unless necessary)
- Prefer functional components and hooks
- Use async/await over promises
- Follow RESTful API conventions
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add comments for complex logic

## Before Making Changes
1. ALWAYS read relevant docs/ files first:
   - docs/system-overview.md
   - docs/domain-model.md
   - docs/api-spec.md
   - docs/ui-spec.md

2. Follow the established patterns
3. Test locally before committing

## MVP Focus
- Start with Business Case document flow end-to-end
- Keep it simple and working
- Add features incrementally
- No authentication in v1 (use fake user)

## Libraries to Use
- Backend: express, prisma, zod (validation), docx (export), pdf-lib (PDF export)
- Frontend: react, react-router-dom, axios, @tanstack/react-query, shadcn/ui, tailwindcss, tip-tap (rich text editor)

## Error Handling
- Always handle errors gracefully
- Show user-friendly error messages
- Log errors server-side
- Use proper HTTP status codes

